{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/123/syllabusSQ08.html", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\r<head>\r  <meta content=\"text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1\"\rhttp-equiv=\"Content-Type\" />\r  <meta http-equiv=\"Author\" content=\"Richard N. Taylor\" />\r  <meta content=\"Taylor IN4MATX 211\" name=\"Keywords\" />\r<title>IN4MATX 123 Spring 2008</title>\r\r  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r  <style type=\"text/css\">\r<!--\r.style1 {color: #666666}\r.style3 {\r\tfont-size: 24px;\r\tcolor: #474B50;\r}\r.style6 {color: #FF0000}\r-->\r  </style>\r</head>\r<body>\r\r\r<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><font face=\"Verdana\">\r\rInformatics 123: Software Architectures, Distributed Systems, and Interoperability</font></h2>\r<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r  <p><font face=\"Verdana\"><b>\r  Spring Quarter 2008</b></font></p>\r  <p><i>Last update:\r      <!-- #BeginDate format:Am1 -->May 29, 2008<!-- #EndDate -->\r  </i></p>\r</div>\r\r&nbsp;<br />\r\r\r<table width=\"60%\" cellspacing=\"8\">\r<tbody>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Instructor:</b></p></td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t<a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/\">Richard N. Taylor </a>\t</p></td>\r</tr>\r\r<tr>\r\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Email:</b></p></td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t(taylor [at] ics [dot] uci [dot] edu)<br />\r\tTo ensure a response to your email, please include\r&quot;Informatics 123&quot; in the\r\tsubject line and send your email from a UCI\raccount.\t</p></td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Office hours:</b>\t</p></td>\r<td> After class, or by email appointment</td>\r</tr>\r\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Lectures: </b></font>\t</p></td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\r\tTuesday and Thursday 12:30-1:50 <strong>p.m,</strong> ICS180</p></td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r  <td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"><strong>TA</strong></td>\r  <td>Rosalva Gallardo (rgallard at uci.edu). Office hours: Tuesday 10-10:50am.\r    DBH 5051.</td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r  <td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Discussion</strong></td>\r  <td>M 1:00-1:50, ICS 180 </td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>Web site:</b></td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/123/syllabusSQ08.html\">http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/123/syllabusSQ08.html</a></td>\r</tr>\r\r<!--\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>EEE Noteboard:</b>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607\">http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607</a><br>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r</tr>\r-->\r</tbody>\r</table>\r\r\r<h3>What's New? </h3>\r<ul>\r  \r  \r  \r  <li>[May 29, 2008] More changes to lecture schedule.</li>\r  <li>[May 27, 2008] Minor update to lecture schedule.</li>\r  <li>[May 19, 2008] Discussion slides and assignment #3 posted.</li>\r  <li>[May 6, 2008] Lecture schedule\r    shuffled.</li>\r  <li>[April 28, 2008] Discussion slides and assignment #2 posted.</li>\r  <li>[April 21, 2008] Slides from today's discussion posted. Class schedule\r    tweaked.</li>\r  <li>[April 14, 2008] Slides from today's discussion posted.</li>\r  <li>[April 7, 2008] First assignment posted + slides from today's discussion\r    section.</li>\r  <li>[March 31, 2008] Website open </li>\r</ul>\r<p><font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"-1\"><a\rhref=\"#description\">Description</a>\r  - <a href=\"#schedule\">Schedule</a> - <a\rhref=\"#grading\">Grading</a>\r  \r- <a href=\"#readings\">Readings</a> - <a\rhref=\"#policies\">Policies</a>\r  \r</font>\r</font></p>\r<hr width=\"100%\" />\r\r<h3>\r<a name=\"description\" id=\"description\"></a><b>Description</b></font></h3>\r<p><b><a\rhref=\"http://www.editor.uci.edu/07-08/ics/ics.4.htm#gen1\">Catalog\rdescription</a>:</b></p>\r\r<p> Prepares students to engineer well-structured software systems. Students\r  learn a wide range of software architectural styles, architectural platforms\r  that provide standard services to applications, and formal architecture description\r  languages. Prerequisites: Informatics 122 or the following: ICS 51 with a grade\r  of C or better; Informatics 101/CS 141/CSE141 and Informatics 111/CSE121; Mathematics\r2A-B and Statistics 67/Mathematics 67.</p>\r<hr width=\"100%\" />\r<h3><a name=\"readings\" id=\"readings\"></a>Textbook and Assigned Readings</h3>\r<p> The following textbook is <em>required</em>; readings will be assigned on a weekly\r  basis.</p>\r<p><strong>Software Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice.</strong> Richard\r  N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, and Eric M. Dashofy. Copyright &copy; 2009 John\rWiley &amp; Sons, Inc. (ISBN: 9780470167748)</p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3><font face=\"Verdana\"><a\rname=\"schedule\"></a></font>Schedule</h3>\r\r<p>\rThe schedule is subject to change.&nbsp;\r\r<table width=100% height=\"968\" border=1 cellpadding=\"3\">\r\r  <tr>\r  \t<th width=\"7%\">Week</th>\r  \t<th colspan=\"2\">Date</th>\r  \t<th width=\"34%\">Topic</th>\r\r  \t<th width=\"13%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"style1\">Readings</th>\r    <th width=\"13%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"style1\">Discussion/Assignments</th>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r  \t<td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"><div align=\"center\">1  \r  \t    <!-- - - - - - - -1- - - - - - - -->\r\r    </div>\r  \t<td width=\"7%\" rowspan=\"9\" class=\"date\"><div align=\"center\">\r      <p>A</p>\r      <p>P</p>\r      <p>R</p>\r      <p>I</p>\r      <p>L</p>\r    </div>      \r      <p align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r  \t<td width=\"7%\" class=\"date\">1&nbsp;Tu\r    <td>The Big Idea\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 1</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r<tr>\r  <td class=\"date\">3&nbsp;Th\r    <td>The Big Idea, continued</td>\r  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">  \r  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">  \r</tr>\r  <tr><td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"><div align=\"center\">2  \r        <!-- - - - - - - -2- - - - - - - -->\r    </div>\r    <td class=\"date\">8&nbsp;Tu\r    <td>Architectures in Context </td>\r  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 2      \r  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"><p><a href=\"INF123_Discussion1.ppt\">Slides</a> from 4/7/08 Discussion.</p>\r    <p><a href=\"Assignment1.html\">Assignment #1</a></p>  \r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">10&nbsp;Th\r    <td>Basic Concepts and Definitions</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 3</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr><td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"><div align=\"center\">3  \r        <!-- - - - - - - -3- - - - - - - -->\r    </div>\r    <td class=\"date\">15&nbsp;Tu\r    <td>Designing Architectures </td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 4</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"><a href=\"INF123_Discussion2.ppt\">Slides</a> from 4/14/08 Discussion.</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">17&nbsp;Th\r\r<!-- <td>Aspect Oriented Programming</td>\r      <td>Lopes</td>\r      <td><a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/ICS221/papers/AOP.pdf\">[KLM+97]</a>\r\t      <br>and optionally\r\t      <br><a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Eredmiles/ics221-FQ03/papers/TDBL00.pdf\">[TDBL00]</a> </td>\r-->\r    <td>Architectural Styles </td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr><td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"><div align=\"center\">4  \r        <!-- - - - - - - -4- - - - - - - -->\r    </div>\r    <td class=\"date\">22&nbsp;Tu</td>\r      <td>Myx and ArchStudio</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"><a href=\"INF123_Discussion3.ppt\">Slides</a> from 4/21/08 Discussion.</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">24&nbsp;Th</td>\r      <td>Styles and Greenfield Design</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 5</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr><td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"><div align=\"